The input string `expression` must be a valid mathematical expression of the form `<num1>+<num2>`.
The length of `expression` must be between 3 and 10.
`expression` must start and end with digits.
`expression` must contain exactly one '+' character.
The original value of `expression`, and the value of `expression` after adding any pair of parentheses that meets the requirements must fit within a signed 32-bit integer.
